Harry B. STILZ, Appellant, v. BETHLEHEM SHIPBUILDING CORPORATION, Limited. No. 9068. Circuit Court of Appeals, Third Circuit. Argued Nov. 21, 1945. Decided Jan. 30, 1946. Harry B. Stilz, pro se, of Philadelphia, Pa., for appellant. Paul & Paul, of Philadelphia, Pa., for appellee.

Before BIGGS, McLAUGHLIN, and O’CONNELL, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

The appellant seeks in effect to set aside a judgment of this court rendered on November 5, 1928, 29 F.2d 156, and has made a motion to such effect. The reasons asserted in support of the motion are inadequate. Accordingly, the motion will be denied.
